Sheffield United's League One fixture with Scunthorpe United has been postponed due to icy conditions at Bramall Lane.

Referee Mark Heywood conducted a pitch inspection at 10am and although he believed the pitch was playable, he was concerned about supporter access in and around the stadium.

'I'm calling the game off on health and safety grounds,' the official was quoted as saying by Sheffield United's official Twitter account.

