Scunthorpe, who lie 17th in the table, were hoping extend their unbeaten run in all competitions to 10 matches.

The Iron are set to play the winners of the outstanding second round FA Cup tie between Chesterfield and MK Dons in the third round. 

Three matches in the Conference also fell victim to the weather, with Telford v Gateshead, Alfreton Town v Dartford and Wrexham v Forest Green all called off following pitch inspections.

 

